post_text:
ATTENTION CLASS OF 2020
Next week, starting on Monday, September 14th, senior yearbooks can be picked up during office hours from 7:30-4. You will buzz in and let them know whose yearbook you are picking up and someone will bring it to you. If you have a sibling in the building, the book will be going home with them. If you are asking someone besides a parent or sibling to pick up your book you will need to email Mrs. Schipper (tschipper@riverdaleschools.org) to let her know who is picking up the book. If you did not purchase a yearbook, you can email Mrs. Schipper to be added to the waitlist or to find out if you purchased a book or not.

shared_text:
Riverdale Golf Team
August 4 at 12:13 AM ¬∑

Hello Riverdale Golfers and Families!

This Thursday, August 6th, we will be hosting our parent information / golfer interest meeting. If you have a returning golfer or have someone interested in joining the team, please meet at the Byron Hills Golf Course pavilion at 5:00PM. We ask that only one representative from each family attend. We will be practicing social distancing.

Due to the expected significant increase in the team enrollment, the Riverdale Golf Program will be limited to 30 individuals total (boys and girls). We will host tryouts August 10th-12th at the course. The tryouts will include playing three 9-hole rounds and taking a rules test.

More details about the season and making the team will be explained at the informational meeting.

Thank you,

Coach Groves
Coach Dennhardt

post_text: Here are the updated guidelines that we have received from the IHSA. We have tried to be as transparent as possible regarding these issues and how they affect our school, community and programs. It will take us a few days to digest this information and formulate our plan with how this will look for our activities. There are still many questions that will need answered. We plan to communicate out when we have a solid plan to share.

post_text:
Attention Spring Sport Athletes,

In conjunction with locker pick-up this Saturday, May 2nd from 9AM - Noon, we would like ask that all spring sport athletes bring all school issued items (uniforms/warm-ups) checked out to them and return them to Coach Dierikx. At this time, there will be tubs to drop off your uniforms .

When you drop off your uniform, we will also have your spring sports pictures ready to hand to you.

Winter sports awards and certificates will be handed out at this time as well.

Baseball players will also be able to pick up their fundraising cookie dough that they sold and be able to distribute to the households in which they sold it to.

I hope everyone is staying safe and healthy during these unique times!

Sincerely,
Coach D

Riverdale Education Foundation is once again sponsoring sports physicals for all Riverdale middle school and high school students. These will be offered on Monday, May 4 from 5:00-6:30 pm at the Riverdale High School gym. These will be good for the entire 2020-21 school year. Cost is $10.

This will not fulfill the requirement for 6th and 9th grade physical forms required by the school and state of Illinois; however, the physical from your doctor will meet the requirement for sports.

shared_text:
Susan Michelle
February 25 at 5:40 PM ¬∑

The Riverdale Girls' Basketball team is in the Illinois 2A State Tournament this weekend for the first time! I have included the game times and coverage in the picture.

This is special, as my Senior year (1976-1977) was the first year for Girls' Basketball at RHS. We started something and these girls are marching now to State. I was on the team that first year, but only remember playing in 1 game and shooting for 1 basket, which I missed. That's OK with me. I was part of something new and special.

CONGRATULATIONS girls!!!

post_text:
RAMS-

Our girls are competing in the Elite 8 Monday night at 7pm in Dekalb. To help cheer on our girls, we are arranging a fan bus for students. The cost is $9 per student and money needs to be turned in before school starts Monday morning. (The $9 covers the $8 entrance fee to the event and the transportation to and from the event). Starting at 4:30 there will be free pizza for those students who ride the bus. The bus will be departing from school at 5 p.m. We anticipate it returning to school between 9:30- 10 p.m.
Make sure you sign up and pay before school Monday if you want to go cheer on our Lady Rams.

*In addition, we also have a fan bus going to Rock Falls on Tuesday for the Wrestlers. The cost is $7 and sign up needs to happen by 8:10 Tuesday morning. The bus will leave at 5pm. Just like for the girls' basketball fan bus we will need 25 HS students signed up and paid for the wrestling fan bus.

Ram fans- our wrestlers have had an outstanding season this year, and the team has advanced to the sweet 16 in State. We are wrestling Dakota at 6 p.m. next Tuesday at Rock Falls High School. We will have a sign-up sheet in the office until Tuesday morning for any student who would like to ride a fan bus to the event. Cost is $7 (and that includes your entry fee into the event). The bus will leave at 5 p.m. from the high school and will return to the high school at approximately 8-8:30 p.m. Announcements will be made Tuesday to let students know if we have enough students sign up to take the fan bus. Make sure you turn in your money to the main office by next Tuesday before school. Let's make an effort to show up and support our wrestlers who are making a State run as a team this year!

Go Rams!

post_text:
Riverdale Speech Team competed in their Regional Tournament on Saturday in Sterling.
Jack Kelley and Eli Mueller placed 2nd in Humorous Duet Acting and will be advancing to Sectionals.
Nick Sidor placed 4th in Impromptu Speaking and will be advancing to Sectionals.
Also placing were Makenzie Jones 6th place Poetry Speaking, Izzy Slone 6th place Original Oratory, Kyan Stuart 7th place Humorous Interpretation, and Haley Kline 7th Place Original Comedy.
